description:
Subjects Addressed: (1) Blessed is he that readeth, and they that hear the words of this prophecy, and keep those things which are written therein: for the time is at hand. Revelation 1:3
(2) Morgan Freeman and National Geographic: The biblical “666” referred to Emperor Nero, (3:10)
(3) What did Jesus, Gabriel, John, and Ellen White go through to give us The Revelation and The Great Controversy? (10:00)
(4) With migrant mission to Greece, Pope Francis cements ties with Orthodox Churches; one of two schisms is now healed. (37:56)
(5) Bernie Sanders forms image to Popery by stressing “common good” in Vatican attack on capitalism. (40:54)
(6) Catholic media and Bob Casey state that “common good” is a Roman Catholic social teaching. (42:45)
(7) Pope Francis persuades the United States and the United Nations to enforce laws based on the “common good.” (45:09)
(8) A.J. Jones reveals that the term “common good” was used to push forward the Sunday Law Bill in the 1800’s. (45:26)
(9) By peace shall he destroy many, Daniel 8:23-25: Vatican to renounce its “just war” doctrine for the “just peace” doctrine. (49:18)
(10) Why Are 2 Different Popes Telling Us to Read “Lord of the World”? (51:22)
(11) Madeleine Albright, former U.S. secretary of state, spoke at Georgetown University: The only way to advance world peace, Jesuitism must be injected into political policies. (54:20)
(12) Barack Obama spoke at Georgetown University: Simply put, this country and this world benefit from your commitment to Jesuit principles. (56:52)
